        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A form of Crigler Najjar syndrome (CNS) a rare hereditary disorder of bilirubin metabolism characterized by unconjugated hyperbilirubinemia due to reduced and inducible activity of hepatic UDP-glucuronosyltransferase 1A1. The disorder clinically manifests with neonatal isolated jaundice with a risk of developing bilirubin encephalopathy later in life due to triggers such as stress or infection."
        },
